The paper deals with social network analysis and clustering, which are topics that fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.SD), systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SOC). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis of social networks and the detection of social circles, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely categories. The use of multi-view social graphs and spectral clustering also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.SD and cs.LG.
